Furthermore please discuss any changes on the talk page first. In particular please discuss any move/deletions first. Edits made without discussion are likely to be reverted quickly. -->
[[File:Bahaullah from miller.jpg|thumb|150px|Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h. Persian inscription reads ''M<U+00ED>rz<U+00E1> <U+1E24>usayn-`Al<U+00ED> N<U+00FA>r<U+00ED>'']]
There are two known photographs of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h.  This photo was taken for passport purposes while he was in [[Adrianople]] (present day [[Edirne]]) and is reproduced in [[William McElwee Miller|William Miller]]'s book on the Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> Faith.  Copies of both pictures are at the [[Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> World Centre]], and one is on display in the [[Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> World Centre buildings#International Archives|International Archives]] building, where the Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED>s view it as part of an organized [[pilgrimage]].  Outside of this experience Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED>s prefer not to view this photo in public, or even to display it in their private homes,<ref name="opi">{{Cite web| url = http://bahai-library.com/uhj_photographs_bahaullah_miller | title = Letter from the Office of Public Information regarding the photograph of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h | author = Office of Public Information | accessdate = 2008-12-20}}</ref> and Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> institutions have requested the press not to publish the image in the media.<ref>{{Cite web| url = http://www.bahai.us/system/files/PublicationPhotosV8.pdf | title = Publication of Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> Photos | accessdate = 2008-12-20 |  publisher = bahai.us | author = United States Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> Office of Communications}}</ref>

Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h's image is not, itself, offensive to Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED>s.  However, Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED>s are expected to treat the image of any [[Manifestation of God]] with extreme reverence. According to this practice, they avoid depictions  [[Depiction of Jesus|of Jesus]] or [[depictions of Muhammad|of Muhammad]], and refrain from portraying any of them in [[Play (theatre)|plays]] and [[drama]]. For example, copies of the photographs are displayed on highly significant occasions, such as six conferences held in October 1967 commemorating the centenary of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h's writing of the ''[[Suriy-i-Mul<U+00FA>k]]'' (Tablet to the Kings), which [[Shoghi Effendi]] describes as "the most momentous Tablet revealed by Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h".<ref>{{Harvnb|Effendi|1944|p=171}}</ref>  After a meeting in Adrianople, the [[Hands of the Cause]] travelled to the conferences, 'each bearing the precious trust of a photograph of the Blessed Beauty, which it will be the privilege of those attending the Conferences to view.'<ref>{{Harvnb|Universal House of Justice|1996|p=105}}</ref>

The official Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> position on displaying the photograph of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h is:

:"There is no objection that the believers look at the picture of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h, but they should do so with the utmost reverence, and should also not allow that it be exposed openly to the public, even in their private homes."
::(From a letter written on behalf of Shoghi Effendi to an individual believer, 6 December 1939)<ref>{{Harvnb|Hornby|1983|p=540}}</ref>

While the above passage clarifies that it is considered disrespectful to display his photograph to the public, regarding postings on other websites the [[Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> World Centre]] has written:

:"For Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED>s, the photograph of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h is very precious and it should not only be viewed but also handled with due reverence and respect, which is not the case here [on a non-Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED> web site]. Thus, it is indeed disturbing to Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED>s to have the image of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h treated in such a disrespectful way. However, as the creator of the site is not a Bah<U+00E1>'<U+00ED>, there is little, if anything, that can be done to address this matter. We hope these comments have been of assistance."
::(Office for Public Information, 4 September 1999, Photo of Bah<U+00E1>'u'll<U+00E1>h on Web Site)<ref name="opi"/>

